Colletotrichum brevisporum (Glomerellaceae)
strain PSSF01 was isolated from a plant stem collected in Baise City ( Guangxi province , China ) at GPS coordinates 23.5445 N , 106.3840 E in November 2018 . The plant was identified by Dr. Tianxiang Li, Tianjin College of Traditional Chinese Medicine, as
Piper sarmentosum Roxb. (Piperaceae)
. First, the plant was washed by water to get rid of soil, then surface sterilization was conducted using 70% ethanol for 1 min, sodium hypochlorite (with 5–10% available chlorite) for 2 min, followed by a rinse of sterile water. The plant was divided into leaf, stem and root, and each section was cut into small pieces ( 2–5 mm ) and placed onto the surface of solid media (
;
). After two weeks, individual colonies were isolated and grown separately on agar plates. The isolated strains are retained in the internal fungal collection at the School of Pharmaceutical Science and Technology.

After fermentation, the fungal culture in each flask was first filtered through cheesecloth, the broth was extracted with EtOAc (400 mL) three times, while the mycelium was extracted with MeOH (200 mL) under ultrasonication. Then the EtOAc extracts and MeOH extracts were combined together and reduced under vacuum to yield a crude extract (
8.73 g
). To remove polar media components, aqueous-organic solvent partitions was conducted on the crude extract using EtOAc and BuOH in turn; the organic fractions were then combined and concentrated under vacuum (Savant SC 210A, Ameritech) to yield an organic-soluble extract (
2.85 g
).

