;
). Calculated UV and ECD spectra were Boltzmann averaged and compared to experimental spectra utilizing SpecDis (
).

Diffraction intensity was collected at 159.99 (10) K on a Rigaku XtaLAB FRX Diffractometer equipped with a Hypix6000HE detector, using Cu Kα radiation (λ = 1.54184 Å). Data reduction was accomplished using program crysAlispro (version 1.171. 
35.45 g
). The structure was solved by intrinsic phasing method using SHELXT and was refined by full-matrix least-squares technique using SHELXL-2015 embedded into OLEX2 1.3. All non-H atoms were refined with anisotropic displacement parameters. H atoms were placed in calculated positions and were refined using a riding model with an isotropic displacement parameter.
